If you are not happy with the amount of coffee that your Nespresso machine provides, you can reset the amounts delivered. Automatic Essenza/Inissia/Citiz/Pixie/Latissima lines can be reset as follows:
- switch on the machine, fill the water tank with potable water; - take a capsule and place a cup under the coffee spout;
- press the coffee button and keep pressing until you have reached the required amount of coffee. This quantity will be the saved in the memory of your machine. In future, your cup will be filled to this new level. The programming can be done any time, for both lungo and espresso buttons.
